frameDefinitions: An Item is in a state of dryness.
The words in this frame refer to what Clothing the Wearer (or a specific Body_part of the Wearer) has on.
A Binding_principle, previously only existing as a concept or formulation, enters an 'active' phase or state.
In this frame, an Agent engages in personal body care by grooming either a Patient or a Body_part.
An Agent causes a Theme to move away from a location, the Source.
These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
frameExamples: I <t>had</t> <t>on</t> the most ridiculous monkey-suit you could imagine.
The new curfew laws <t>kicked in</t> last weekend.
I saw that several men in dark suits had <t>removed</t> all of the evidence from the scene.
The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The person whose clothing is under discussion.
This role identifies the <fen>Clothing</fen> that the <fen>Wearer</fen> wears.
The body part of the <fen>Wearer</fen> which is covered by the <fen>Clothing</fen>.
The time at or during which the <fen>Wearer</fen> has the <fen>Clothing</fen> on.
When the <fen>Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Event</fen> takes place.
The agent is the person who does the grooming.
The patient is the person who gets washed.
This is the region of the body that gets groomed.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
Theme is the object that changes location.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the <fen>Theme</fen>, before it changes location.
The non-Agentive cause of the removing event.
The time at which the removal takes place.
The location where the removal takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
